			<h2>Travis Scott</h2>
			<p>Travis Scott, born Jacques Berman Webster II on April 30, 1992, is an American rapper, singer, songwriter, and record producer from Houston, Texas. He is best known for his unique style of hip-hop music, which incorporates elements of trap, psychedelic music, and rock.
Scott began his career in music in 2008, when he formed a group called The Graduates with his friend Chris Holloway. The group released their first EP in 2009, but disbanded soon after. In 2012, Scott moved to Los Angeles to pursue his music career, and soon after signed a deal with Kanye West's GOOD Music label.
Scott released his debut mixtape, "Owl Pharaoh," in 2013, which was well-received by critics and fans alike. He followed up with his second mixtape, "Days Before Rodeo," in 2014, which further solidified his place in the music industry.
In 2015, Scott signed a deal with Epic Records and released his debut studio album, "Rodeo," which featured collaborations with Kanye West, The Weeknd, and Justin Bieber. The album debuted at number three on the US Billboard 200 chart and was certified platinum by the Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA).
Scott's second studio album, "Birds in the Trap Sing McKnight," was released in 2016 and debuted at number one on the US Billboard 200 chart. The album featured collaborations with artists such as Kendrick Lamar, Quavo, and Young Thug.
In 2018, Scott released his third studio album, "Astroworld," which was named after a now-defunct amusement park in Houston. The album was a critical and commercial success, debuting at number one on the US Billboard 200 chart and earning Scott his first Grammy nomination for Best Rap Album.
In addition to his music career, Scott has also collaborated with several brands in the fashion industry, including Nike, Jordan, and Helmut Lang. He has also been involved in several philanthropic efforts, including donating profits from merchandise sales to the Hurricane Harvey relief efforts in his hometown of Houston.
In his personal life, Scott has been in a high-profile relationship with reality TV star Kylie Jenner since 2017. The couple welcomed their first child, a daughter named Stormi, in 2018.
Overall, Travis Scott has become one of the most influential and successful artists of his generation, known for his unique style and innovative approach to music. His music has inspired and influenced countless other artists in the hip-hop and rap genres, and he continues to push the boundaries of what is possible in the world of music and fashion.</p>
		</div>
