			<h2>Post Malone</h2>
			<p>Post Malone, whose real name is Austin Richard Post, is an American rapper, singer, songwriter, and record producer. He was born on July 4, 1995, in Syracuse, New York, but spent most of his childhood in Grapevine, Texas.
Post Malone's interest in music started at an early age. He began playing the guitar at the age of 14 and started producing music shortly after. He attended Tarrant County College but dropped out before completing his degree to pursue a career in music.
In 2015, Post Malone released his debut single, "White Iverson," which quickly gained popularity and became a viral hit on social media platforms like SoundCloud and YouTube. The song eventually caught the attention of Republic Records, and he signed a recording contract with them later that year.
In August 2016, Post Malone released his debut studio album, "Stoney." The album featured hit singles such as "Congratulations" and "Go Flex" and debuted at number six on the US Billboard 200 chart. The album was eventually certified triple platinum by the Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA).
In April 2018, Post Malone released his second studio album, "Beerbongs & Bentleys." The album featured hit singles such as "Rockstar" and "Psycho" and debuted at number one on the US Billboard 200 chart. The album was certified quadruple platinum by the RIAA and earned Post Malone several award nominations, including for Album of the Year at the 2019 Grammy Awards.
In September 2019, Post Malone released his third studio album, "Hollywood's Bleeding." The album featured hit singles such as "Circles" and "Wow" and debuted at number one on the US Billboard 200 chart. The album was certified triple platinum by the RIAA and earned Post Malone several award nominations, including for Record of the Year and Best Pop Solo Performance for "Circles" at the 2021 Grammy Awards.
Post Malone's music is often described as a blend of hip-hop, R&B, and rock. His unique style and sound have earned him a large following and critical acclaim. He has been praised for his ability to seamlessly blend different genres and create music that appeals to a wide range of listeners.
Aside from his music career, Post Malone has also dabbled in acting, appearing in the 2020 Netflix film "Spenser Confidential." He has also collaborated with several brands and companies, including Bud Light and Crocs, to create limited-edition merchandise and products.
Despite his success, Post Malone has been open about his struggles with mental health and substance abuse. He has been vocal about his use of marijuana and has admitted to struggling with anxiety and depression. However, he has also been an advocate for mental health awareness and has encouraged others to seek help when needed.
Overall, Post Malone's unique sound, eclectic style, and ability to blend different genres have made him a standout artist in the music industry. His continued success and influence are a testament to his talent and hard work.
</p>
