			<h2>Ariana Grande</h2>
			<p>Ariana Grande-Butera, better known as Ariana Grande, is a popular American singer, songwriter, and actress. She was born on June 26, 1993, in Boca Raton, Florida. She is the daughter of Joan Grande, the CEO of Hose-McCann Communications, and Edward Butera, a graphic designer. Ariana's parents separated when she was just eight years old, and she was raised by her mother.
Ariana began performing at a young age and made her debut in the Broadway musical "13" in 2008. She then went on to star in the Nickelodeon television series "Victorious" and its spin-off, "Sam & Cat." Her role on "Victorious" helped to launch her music career, and she released her debut album, "Yours Truly," in 2013.
"Yours Truly" debuted at number one on the Billboard 200, and its lead single, "The Way," featuring rapper Mac Miller, became a top ten hit. The album's success established Ariana as a rising star in the music industry.
She continued her success with her second album, "My Everything," released in 2014. The album featured the hit singles "Problem" and "Break Free," and debuted at number one on the Billboard 200. Ariana embarked on her first headlining tour, The Honeymoon Tour, in support of the album.
Ariana's third album, "Dangerous Woman," was released in 2016 and debuted at number two on the Billboard 200. The album's title track became a top ten hit, and the album also featured collaborations with Nicki Minaj, Lil Wayne, and Future. Ariana embarked on her second headlining tour, the Dangerous Woman Tour, in support of the album.
In 2018, Ariana released her fourth album, "Sweetener," which debuted at number one on the Billboard 200. The album's lead single, "No Tears Left to Cry," became a hit, and the album also featured collaborations with Pharrell Williams and Nicki Minaj. Ariana embarked on her third headlining tour, the Sweetener World Tour, in support of the album.
Ariana's fifth album, "Thank U, Next," was released in 2019 and debuted at number one on the Billboard 200. The album featured the hit singles "Thank U, Next" and "7 Rings," and Ariana became the first artist since The Beatles to have three songs debut at number one on the Billboard Hot 100 in the same year. She embarked on her fourth headlining tour, the Sweetener/Thank U, Next World Tour, in support of the album.
In addition to her successful music career, Ariana has also acted in several films and television shows, including "Zoolander 2," "Hairspray Live!," and "Scream Queens." She has also been involved in various charitable causes, including the fight against cancer, animal rights, and LGBTQ rights.
Ariana has won numerous awards throughout her career, including two Grammy Awards, and has been recognized for her vocal range and powerful vocals. She has also been praised for her authenticity and vulnerability in her music, and her ability to connect with her fans.
In conclusion, Ariana Grande is a talented and accomplished artist who has made a significant impact on the music industry. Her music, acting, and philanthropic efforts have earned her a dedicated fanbase and numerous accolades, and she continues to be a major force in pop culture.</p>
