			<h2>Justin Bieber</h2>
			<p>Justin Bieber is a Canadian singer, songwriter, and actor who rose to fame in the late 2000s as a teen heartthrob. Born on March 1, 1994, in London, Ontario, Bieber was raised by his mother, Pattie Mallette, who was just 18 years old at the time of his birth. His father, Jeremy Bieber, left the family when Justin was just a toddler.
Bieber's love for music started at a young age, and he learned to play the piano, drums, guitar, and trumpet on his own. In 2007, he began posting videos of himself singing cover songs on YouTube, which quickly gained popularity. It was not long before he was discovered by talent manager Scooter Braun, who helped him land a record deal with Island Records.
Bieber's debut album, "My World 2.0," was released in 2010 and featured hit singles like "Baby," "Somebody to Love," and "U Smile." The album debuted at number one on the US Billboard 200 chart and made Bieber the youngest solo male artist to top the chart since Stevie Wonder in 1963.
Over the years, Bieber has continued to release hit albums and singles, including "Believe," "Purpose," "Sorry," and "Love Yourself." He has collaborated with numerous other artists, such as Ed Sheeran, DJ Khaled, and Ariana Grande.
Bieber's personal life has also been a subject of media attention. He has been involved in several legal issues, including vandalism, DUI, and assault. He has also been open about his struggles with mental health, including depression and anxiety.
In 2018, Bieber surprised fans by announcing his engagement to model Hailey Baldwin, whom he had dated on and off since 2015. The couple married later that year in a private ceremony in New York City. In 2019, Bieber took a break from music to focus on his health and personal life, but he returned to the spotlight in 2020 with his fifth studio album, "Changes."
In addition to his music career, Bieber has also ventured into acting. He has appeared in films like "Zoolander 2" and "Killing Hasselhoff," as well as TV shows like "CSI: Crime Scene Investigation" and "Saturday Night Live."
Overall, Justin Bieber has become one of the biggest pop stars of his generation, with a devoted fan base and a string of hit songs to his name. Despite his personal struggles, he has continued to make music and remains a beloved figure in the entertainment industry.</p>
